# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   It makes the environment reproducible in most cases.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different OS, they may get conflicts.
# .env
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock can be submitted to version control or not.
#   https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock can be submitted to version control or not.
# pdm.lock

